Dear Tom,<p>

The film Heaven and Earth was released in 1993, about two months before I
went to Viet Nam. I had heard about helicopter-related executions of Viet Cong 
for several years before, so my thinking was not influenced by Oliver Stone's
film version.
<p>
Also, it is easy to fake photographs. In my opinion, the photographic evidence for helicopter-related executions in the War Crimes Museum in Ho Chi Minh City (Saigon) did not specifically prove anything: the example on display could have been real or could have been faked.
<p>
But hearing a seminar speaker last week state to me, specifically, that helicopter-related interrogation executions had occurred--because he knew--reinforced the possibility that the photograph in the museum was real and not faked.
<p>
Perhaps one reason why the war continues to haunt certain Americans is because of their war-related behaviors at the time.
<p>
Tom, the intent of my message was not to inflame your passion.
<p>
Regards,<br>
